@account
clear
color blue
*say 0 ###### What you get in your account ######
color black
*say 0 You have two username and password combinations in your account.
*say 0 The first is called your main account and is for a service on port 23, this offers:
*say 0 you can login to a filemanager program from which you can upload and download files. This program
*say 0 also offers the ability to change properties on a file, assign password protection and hide files.
*say 0 From here you can also encrypt files using our own custom written encryption. Account maintenance
*say 0 such as changing your password can be done here. 
*say 0 This account also acts as an email address and using our simple email program you can move attatchments
*say 0 to your file hosting area.
*say 0  ---
*say 0 Your second is called your filesharing account and is for a service on port 625, this offers:
*say 0 This service is simply for filedownloading. Using your second username and password combination you
*say 0 can quickly retrieve files for when you don't want to use the main program. Since this program
*say 0 is only for downloading you can give this password to others so they can download shared files.
*say 0  ---
*say 0 You will also have access to 24 hour tech support so that should you have any problem at any time we
*say 0 will be able to solve it for you
color red
*say 0 Press any key to go back
pause
goto product

